01/12/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The parliament of Republika Srpska (RS) approved on Thursday (November 30th) a new entity government, led by incumbent Prime Minister Milorad Dodik. Out of the 16 cabinet ministers, there are only five new faces. In his address to parliament, Dodik outlined a series of reforms, focusing on the economic sector and living standards. 
In other news Thursday, RS police arrested former Interior Minister Perica Bundalo for racketeering. Investigators say he funnelled illegally obtained money to his Party for Democratic Progress. Bundalo is currently a member of the RS parliament. (Nezavisne Novine - 01/12/06; Fena, PBS, RTRS - 30/11/06)
